            "description": "Two-loop two-point kite topology with two equal-mass internal propagators and three massless internal propagators, depending on $s=p_1^2$. Worked example illustrating the d-log projection / intersection-number construction of the canonical DE coefficient matrix, computed via both the regulator method and relative twisted cohomology on the maximal cut. Four d-log master integrands $\\varphi_1..\\varphi_4$ constructed in Eq. (5.4); LO intersection-number matrix $\\eta$ and its inverse (Eqs. 5.20, 5.23) yield the $d\\Omega$ matrix. No explicit epsilon expansion performed; the result is the d-log DE only.",
